<paragraph id="8B863684FFAD347BFF50F8B2FA9C822D" blockId="4.[159,762,1455,1948]" lastBlockId="4.[826,1429,1209,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">
Diagnosis — P-3 distal setae pectinated, mediodistal seta inserted close to the ventrodistal seta. The ventral seta insertions divide the ventral margin of P-4 into 1: 1: 1 (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAD347BFBE8FB35FB3583C6" box="[1149,1241,1209,1233]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="4.[159,171,1125,1144]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): A – Ventral view; B – Palp; C – Gnathosoma; D – Genital field. Scale bars: A–D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404216/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Medial suture Cx-I/II almost equal in length (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAD347BFB3CFB50FAEF83E3" box="[1193,1283,1244,1268]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="4.[159,171,1125,1144]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): A – Ventral view; B – Palp; C – Gnathosoma; D – Genital field. Scale bars: A–D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404216/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Coxal field extended and the posterior margin of Cx-IV almost reaching to the posterior end of the genital field.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAD347BFCF5FADFFA79808A" blockId="4.[826,1429,1209,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">
Description — Male (n = 2). Colour yellowishbrown. Idiosoma almost round in outline, 713 (700) in L and 653 (610) in W. Integument smooth on the dorsal surface, palps, legs, and coxal field with reticulated frame work (mesh size 8 – 13). Coxal field extending and almost embracing the posterior margin of the genital field; Coxal field 755 (760) in L, 660 (650) in W; Cx-I/II ML 194 (205) / 205 (188), ratio 0.95 (1.09); Cx-II narrow, posterior margin approximately 19 (25) in W, posteromedial margin of Cx- IV forming a right angle. Genital field with three pairs of acetabula, the first two pairs rectangular, and the third pair almost round in outline (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAD347BFABAF974FA648007" box="[1327,1416,1784,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="4.[159,171,1125,1144]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): A – Ventral view; B – Palp; C – Gnathosoma; D – Genital field. Scale bars: A–D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404216/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Length of acetabula: Ac-1, 60 (53); Ac-2, 50 (51); Ac- 3, 37 (38); genital flap 179 (165) in L; genital field 155 (140) in W. Excretory pore smooth. Capitulum ventral L 190 (198), chelicera L 255 (275) (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAD347BFABEF808FA64808A" box="[1323,1416,1924,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="4.[159,171,1125,1144]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): A – Ventral view; B – Palp; C – Gnathosoma; D – Genital field. Scale bars: A–D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404216/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF46660CFFAC347AFEABF82BFB1A80AD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404218" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5404218" box="[318,1270,1959,1978]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404218/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" startId="5.[318,330,1959,1978]" targetBox="[244,1341,330,1813]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAC347AFEABF82BFB1A80AD" blockId="5.[318,1270,1959,1978]" box="[318,1270,1959,1978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">
FIGURE 4: 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAC347AFE36F82BFD4680AD" authorityName="Wang &amp; Jin &amp; Guo" authorityYear="2016" box="[419,682,1959,1978]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extendia" subGenus="Pilolebertia">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAC347AFE36F82BFE0480AD" box="[419,488,1959,1978]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Lebertia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAC347AFE61F82BFDB980AD" box="[500,597,1959,1978]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">Pilolebertia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAC347AFDF7F82BFD4680AD" box="[610,682,1959,1978]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="125">extendia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Male): E – III-L-1 – 6; F – IV-L-1 – 6. Scale bars: E–F = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAF3479FF0AFEBBFE7E81FA" blockId="6.[159,762,311,1773]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">
Numbers of swimming setae: II-L-5, 6 (8); III-L-4, 6 (7); III-L-5, 7 (10); IV-L-4, 9 (7); IV-L-5, 10 (8). IV-L- 1 with one dorsal and two dorsodistal setae. Ventral setae on L-III-IV (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAF3479FE08FE2CFDC686AF" box="[413,554,416,440]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="5.[318,330,1959,1978]" captionTargetBox="[244,1341,330,1813]" captionTargetId="figure-6@5.[227,1361,302,1927]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): E – III-L-1 – 6; F – IV-L-1 – 6. Scale bars: E–F = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404218" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404218/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Figs. 4E, 4F</figureCitation>
): III-L-1, 1 (1); III- L-2, 1 (2); III-L-3, 1 (1); III-L-4, 3 (3); III-L-5, 6 (7) (two strong and peg-like, others hair-like); III-L-6, 7 (8) (hair-like); IV-L-1, 1 (1); IV-L-2, 1 (1); IV-L-3, 1 (1); IV-L-4, 3 (3); IV-L-5, 6 (6); IV-L-6, 3 (3). P-2 with five setae, the ventral seta as long as or even slightly longer than the ventral length of P-2; P-3 distal setae pectinated, dorsal setae separated from each other, the mediodistal seta inserted close to the ventrodistal seta (distance approximately 9 – 11); P- 4 distally narrowed with four fine dorsal setae and one minute peg-like seta (
<quantity id="4CC19B61FFAF3479FE40FCAEFDC1842D" box="[469,557,802,826]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" unit="in" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3 – 4 in</quantity>
length), the ventral seta insertions divided the ventral margin into 1: 1: 1 (
<figureCitation id="13022A01FFAF3479FF6BFCE4FEB68497" box="[254,346,872,896]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="4.[159,171,1125,1144]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[227,1361,302,1093]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3: Lebertia (Pilolebertia) extendia (Male): A – Ventral view; B – Palp; C – Gnathosoma; D – Genital field. Scale bars: A–D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404216/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). P-2/P-4 0.95 (0.89) in L and total length of palp 410 (470). L/H of the palp: P-1, 31 (38)/53 (54), ratio 0.58 (0.70); P-2, 119 (133)/75 (88), ratio 1.59 (1.51); P-3, 100 (115)/63 (64), ratio 1.59 (1.80); P-4, 125 (150)/43 (48), ratio 2.90 (3.13); P-5, 38 (40)/16 (18), ratio 2.38 (2.22). L/H of legs: I-L-1, 75 (88)/50 (70), ratio 1.5 (1.26); I-L-2, 105 (145)/68 (73), ratio 1.54 (1.99); I-L-3, 118 (125)/60 (68), ratio 1.97 (1.84); I-L-4, 175 (175)/58 (60), ratio 3.02 (2.92); I-L-5, 163 (183)/45 (48), ratio 3.62 (3.81); I-L-6, 150 (160)/38 (38), ratio 3.95 (4.21); II-L-1, 63 (80)/63 (75), ratio 1.00 (1.07); II-L-2, 108 (113)/75 (80), ratio 1.44 (1.41); II-L-3, 108 (138)/65 (75), ratio 1.66 (1.84); II- L-4, 188 (208)/58 (70), ratio 3.14 (2.97); II-L-5, 218 (230)/45 (55), ratio 4.84 (4.18); II-L-6, 188 (213)/45 (50), ratio 4.18 (4.26); III-L-1, 86 (80)/65 (78), ratio 1.32 (1.03); III-L-2, 147 (140)/78 (80), ratio 1.88 (1.75); III-L-3, 159 (175)/72 (73), ratio 2.21 (2.40); III- L-4, 252 (245)/70 (68), ratio 3.60 (3.60); III-L-5, 263 (288)/53 (58), ratio 4.96 (4.97); III-L-6, 247 (238)/61 (55), ratio 4.05 (4.33); IV-L-1, 174 (185)/101 (98), ratio 1.72 (1.89); IV-L-2, 166 (148)/86 (85), ratio 1.93 (1.74); IV-L-3, 197 (205)/85 (78), ratio 2.32 (2.63); IV- L-4, 278 (275)/76 (70), ratio 3.66 (3.93); IV-L-5, 274 (300)/63 (63), ratio 4.35 (4.76); IV-L-6, 246 (265)/66 (65), ratio 3.73 (4.08).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAF3479FF50F885FE8E807F" blockId="6.[159,762,1801,1896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Etymology — &quot;Extend&quot; means &quot;enlarge&quot;, the new species is named after the enlarged posterior margin of Cx-IV.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAF3479FF50F808FB2B8682" blockId="6.[197,762,1924,1948]" lastBlockId="6.[826,1429,311,1192]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Remarks — The new species can be distinguished from other species by the mediodistal seta inserted close to the ventrodistal seta and the extended posterior margin of Cx-IV.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C323650FFFAF3479FCF5FE21FBC88331" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAF3479FCF5FE21FB2984E1" blockId="6.[826,1429,311,1192]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FCF5FE21FA9F86D2" authority="Neuman, 1880" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[864,1395,429,453]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis" subGenus="Pilolebertia">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FCF5FE21FC5A86D2" box="[864,950,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Lebertia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FC58FE21FBAB86D2" box="[973,1095,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Pilolebertia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FBC8FE21FB5F86D3" box="[1117,1203,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">insignis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B75FFAF3479FB54FE21FA9F86D2" author="Neuman C. J." box="[1217,1395,429,453]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 123" refId="ref4473" refString="Neuman C. J. 1880 - Om Sveriges Hydrachnider - Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, 17 (3): 1 - 123." type="journal article" year="1880">Neuman, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the new species in the position of the mediodistal seta on P-3 and the distributions of ventral setae on P-4. Nevertheless, there are still many differences: 1) medial suture Cx-I is slightly longer than Cx-II in 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FC4CFDD1FBA08563" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[985,1100,605,628]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FC4CFDD1FBA08563" box="[985,1100,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="4CC19B61FFAF3479FBCEFDD0FB378563" box="[1115,1243,604,628]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.302" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" unit="in" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2 – 1.3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FB76FDD1FABA8563" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[1251,1366,605,628]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FB76FDD1FABA8563" box="[1251,1366,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but in the new species medial sutures Cx-I/II are almost equal in length (ML 0.95); 2) P-2 of the new species is slightly longer than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FB09FD4AFAE385CA" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[1180,1295,710,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FB09FD4AFAE385CA" box="[1180,1295,710,733]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P-2/P-4 L 
<quantity id="4CC19B61FFAF3479FCAFFD64FC218417" box="[826,973,744,768]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0066" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.9812" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" unit="in" value="0.79" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.78">0.78 – 0.80 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FC46FD65FBA88417" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[979,1092,745,768]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FC46FD65FBA88417" box="[979,1092,745,768]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<quantity id="4CC19B61FFAF3479FBE8FD64FB258417" box="[1149,1225,744,768]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.413" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" unit="in" value="0.95">0.95 in</quantity>
the new species); 3) the Cx-IV posterior margin is truncated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FACDFC80FC958451" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FACDFC80FC958451" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the new species the coxal field extends with the posterior margin of Cx-IV almost reaching to the posterior end of the genital field; 4) II- L-5 with 2 swimming setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D07FFAF3479FB31FC14FAFB84B8" authorityName="Neuman" authorityYear="1880" box="[1188,1303,920,943]" class="Arachnida" family="Lebertiidae" genus="Lebertia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FB31FC14FAFB84B8" box="[1188,1303,920,943]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">L. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the new species has 6 – 10 swimming setae on II-L-5. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B75FFAF3479FCD4FC52FC0C84E1" author="Gerecke R." box="[833,992,990,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref3986" refString="Gerecke R. 2009 - Revisional studies on the European species of the water mite genus Lebertia Neuman 1880 (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Lebertiidae) - Abh. Senckenb. Ges. Naturforsch., 566: 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2009">Gerecke 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B75FFAF3479FC7EFC52FB5584E1" author="Bursali A. &amp; Asci F. &amp; Ozkan M." box="[1003,1209,990,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126" pagination="27 - 30" refId="ref3912" refString="Bursali A., Asci F., Ozkan M. 2011 - Lebertia insignis Neuman, 1880 (Acari, Hydrachnidia, Lebertiidae), a new record for the Turkish fauna - Turk. Entomol. Derg., 1 (1): 27 - 30." type="journal article" year="2011">
Bursali 
<emphasis id="B94DEA96FFAF3479FBD1FC53FB9D84E1" box="[1092,1137,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B863684FFAF3479FCF5FB82FBC88331" blockId="6.[826,1429,311,1192]" box="[864,1060,1038,1062]" pageId="6" pageNumber="126">Female unkown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
